(626, 260, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:11:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:4:\"9999\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:4:\"7499\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"3\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"2\";s:10:\"trip_facts\";a:4:{s:8:\"field_id\";a:2:{i:1;s:14:\"transportation\";i:3;s:8:\"altitude\";}s:10:\"field_type\";a:2:{i:1;s:4:\"text\";i:3;s:4:\"text\";}i:1;a:1:{i:1;s:11:\"1-12 people\";}i:3;a:1:{i:3;s:8:\"Moderate\";}}s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:4:{i:1;s:26:\"Delhi To Shimla.  (350 KM)\";i:2;s:12:\"Shimla Local\";i:3;s:40:\"Shimla Kufri &amp; Jakhoo Temple Shimla.\";i:4;s:35:\"Shimla To Delhi Departure. (350 KM)\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:4:{i:1;s:163:\"Arrival at ISBT KASHMIRI GATE Delhi Dep Time at (09:00 PM &amp; 10:00 PM) . From there you proceed for Shimla by Volvo A/C Bus. Overnight  Journey. (8 hrs Journey)\";i:2;s:706:\"On Arrival at shimla bus stand pick up &amp; transfer to hotel &amp; check in to the Hotel, Afternoon half day city tour visiting “INDIAN INSTITUTE OF ADVANCE STUDIES” At 1983m, this magnificent English renaissance structure was the former Vice regal Lodge. Evening free to stroll in the famous shopping place of Shimla town – “The Mall &amp; THE RIDGE” This large open space in the heart of town presents excellent views of the mountain ranges. Shimla\'s landmarks - the neo- gothic structure of Christ Church and the neo - Tudor library building - are worth seeing. Over night stay at Shimla.( ADVANCE STUDY, SANKAT MOCHAN TEMPLE, VAISHNO DEVI GUFA, HIMALAYAN BIRD PARK &amp; BY WALK MALL ROAD )\";i:3;s:596:\"After breakfast full Day Excursion Visiting To “Kufri” India\'s One Of The Best Holiday Paradise Kufri In Shimla Is Beautifully Tucked On An Altitude Of 2,622 Meter, Via Green Valley, Wild Flower Hall, Indira Holiday Home And Fagu. Its lawns and woodland are added attractions. “JAKHOO TEMPLE” At 2455m, this is the town\'s highest peak and a famous point for Shimla\'s famous views. The summit is crowned with a temple dedicated to Lord Hanuman.” Overnight stay at Shimla. ( GREEN VALLEY, WILD FLOWER HALL, HALI PAD, KUFRI, INDIRA TOURIST PARK, MINI ZOO, FAGU VALLEY &amp; JAKHOO TEMPLE )\";i:4;s:74:\"After Breakfast leave for Delhi by Volvo A/C Bus. (8.30 AM &amp; 11.15 AM)\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:4:{i:1;s:182:\"&lt;p&gt;Arrival at ISBT KASHMIRI GATE Delhi Dep Time at (09:00 PM &amp; 10:00 PM) . From there you proceed for Shimla by Volvo A/C Bus. Overnight  Journey. (8 hrs Journey)&lt;/p&gt;\";i:2;s:725:\"&lt;p&gt;On Arrival at shimla bus stand pick up &amp; transfer to hotel &amp; check in to the Hotel, Afternoon half day city tour visiting “INDIAN INSTITUTE OF ADVANCE STUDIES” At 1983m, this magnificent English renaissance structure was the former Vice regal Lodge. Evening free to stroll in the famous shopping place of Shimla town – “The Mall &amp; THE RIDGE” This large open space in the heart of town presents excellent views of the mountain ranges. Shimla\'s landmarks - the neo- gothic structure of Christ Church and the neo - Tudor library building - are worth seeing. Over night stay at Shimla.( ADVANCE STUDY, SANKAT MOCHAN TEMPLE, VAISHNO DEVI GUFA, HIMALAYAN BIRD PARK &amp; BY WALK MALL ROAD )&lt;/p&gt;\";i:3;s:615:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast full Day Excursion Visiting To “Kufri” India\'s One Of The Best Holiday Paradise Kufri In Shimla Is Beautifully Tucked On An Altitude Of 2,622 Meter, Via Green Valley, Wild Flower Hall, Indira Holiday Home And Fagu. Its lawns and woodland are added attractions. “JAKHOO TEMPLE” At 2455m, this is the town\'s highest peak and a famous point for Shimla\'s famous views. The summit is crowned with a temple dedicated to Lord Hanuman.” Overnight stay at Shimla. ( GREEN VALLEY, WILD FLOWER HALL, HALI PAD, KUFRI, INDIRA TOURIST PARK, MINI ZOO, FAGU VALLEY &amp; JAKHOO TEMPLE )&lt;/p&gt;\";i:4;s:112:\"&lt;p&gt;After Breakfast leave for Delhi by Volvo A/C Bus. (8.30 AM &amp; 11.15 AM)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Includes\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:307:\"Welcome drinks on arrival in hotels.\r\n02 Nights accommodation on twin sharing basis.\r\n02 Breakfast and 2 Dinner in Hotel.\r\nDelhi-Shimla-Delhi by Volvo A/C Bus.\r\n03 Days individual Alto / Indica car for Shimla Sight Seeing.\r\nShimla bus stand to Hotel Pickup &amp; Dropping.\r\nAll taxes inclusive in this cost.\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:442:\"&lt;li&gt;Welcome drinks on arrival in hotels.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;02 Nights accommodation on twin sharing basis.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;02 Breakfast and 2 Dinner in Hotel.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Delhi-Shimla-Delhi by Volvo A/C Bus.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;03 Days individual Alto / Indica car for Shimla Sight Seeing.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Shimla bus stand to Hotel Pickup &amp; Dropping.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All taxes inclusive in this cost.&lt;/li&gt;\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Excludes\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:182:\"Monuments entry fees and camera fees.\r\nAny which is not mentioned in above package cost.\r\nAny Guide fees/entrainment fees\r\nAny Air and train fare\r\nSt.4.5% Extra in each tour Packages\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:279:\"&lt;li&gt;Monuments entry fees and camera fees.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any which is not mentioned in above package cost.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Guide fees/entrainment fees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Air and train fare&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;St.4.5% Extra in each tour Packages&lt;/li&gt;\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Frequently asked Questions\";s:9:\"faq_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:40:\"How fit do I need to be to do this trek?\";i:2;s:70:\"How long do we walk every day when doing Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:3;s:50:\"What is the highest altitude reached in this trek?\";i:4;s:54:\"What about battery charging and hot shower facilities?\";i:5;s:49:\"Are there ATMs on the way to Annapurna Base Camp?\";i:6;s:27:\"What about internet access?\";i:7;s:80:\"Is it necessary to hire Guides/trekking agency for Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:8;s:36:\"How much do guides and porters cost?\";}s:11:\"faq_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:265:\"Annapurna Base Camp is a Grade B or a moderately difficult trekking route. So any fit person can do this trek, even if you do not have any previous experience. You should be aware of what to expect and mentally prepare for it. Then, as long as you will to, you can.\";i:2;s:131:\"On average, you walk about 4 to 6 hours per day. One or two days can be as less as 3hrs and one or two days can be as long as 7hrs.\";i:3;s:131:\"The highest altitude reached is 4190m. This is the elevation of Annapurna Base Camp. ABC is the highest we will climb in this trek.\";i:4;s:230:\"Yes, you can charge batteries en route. Charger should be brought. There are hot shower facilities as well. You may have to pay certain amount for both ($1-$2). Negotiate. Also, hot water facility could be free at lower elevation.\";i:5;s:240:\"No. There are no ATMs on this trek route. You will have to draw enough cash in Pokhara or Kathmandu. There are a number of ATMs in these cities. Everything is paid in Nepali rupees. So money should be exchanged before the start of the trek.\";i:6;s:191:\"Yes. Internet can be accessed in most places. Sometimes, there might be some technical problems. Internet in Nepal is not as fast as you are used to and at times you can just lose connection.\";i:7;s:547:\"Not really. It depends on you. If you want, ABC trekking can be done independently. You could hire a guide and a porter by yourself instead of going through an agency or not hire a guide at all. Although, not having a guide can be a little problematic during off season.\r\n\r\nIt really depends on you. Is it your first time in Nepal? How confident are you of being able to find your way around? How pressed on time are you? If you go through an agency, it will be costlier but everything will be planned. You will only have to come, trek and return.\";i:8;s:103:\"For Annapurna region, pay for guides range from $20 to $30 per day and porters take $15 to $25 per day.\";}}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
