(653, 265, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:11:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:4:\"8999\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:4:\"5799\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"4\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"3\";s:10:\"trip_facts\";a:4:{s:8:\"field_id\";a:2:{i:1;s:14:\"transportation\";i:3;s:8:\"altitude\";}s:10:\"field_type\";a:2:{i:1;s:4:\"text\";i:3;s:4:\"text\";}i:1;a:1:{i:1;s:28:\"Via Volvo or Individual Taxi\";}i:3;a:1:{i:3;s:8:\"Moderate\";}}s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:5:{i:1;s:34:\"Delhi to Manali (570 Km 13-14 Hrs)\";i:2;s:37:\"Manali arrival+ Pick up + sightseeing\";i:3;s:34:\"Manali- (up to snow line) - Manali\";i:4;s:31:\"Manali- Kullu valley- Manikaran\";i:5;s:36:\"Manali – Delhi (570 kms 13-14 hrs)\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:5:{i:1;s:251:\"MEALS: No Meal \r\nEvening take the Volvo bus at 05:00 PM from Majnu ka tilla metro station or as directed by us and board to Manali. Overnight journey by Volvo. \r\nREPORTING TIME: 05:00 PM \r\nDEPARTURE TIME: 05:30 PM (There might be delay of 30-45 mints)\";i:2;s:761:\"MEALS: DINNER ONLY. \r\nArrive Manali in the morning, on arrival pick up by company vehicle and transfer to your respected hotel, check in hotel. After fresh up and breakfast, proceed for Manali Sightseeing which includes Hadimba Devi temple is a four-tiered pagoda-like wooden temple standing in deodar trees and has beautiful carvings on its ornamental door. Dedicated to Hadimba, the wife of Bhim, this temple is the venue for an annual fair held during May. Natural Vashisth [known for medicinal use] is located across the Beas River, about 3 km away from Manali, at an altitude of 1,982 meters (6,200 feet) and is the natural sulphur hot springs. Club House, Tibetan Monastery, Van Vihar and The Mall Road back to hotel, dinner and rest overnight in leisure.\";i:3;s:583:\"MEALS: Breakfast and dinner only \r\nAfter breakfast visit to Rohtang Pass/ Snow Point (Situated about 51 km from Manali town at an altitude of 4,111 meters (13,400 ft.) on the highway to Keylong, is Rohtang Pass. Here one sees the majesty of the mountains at its height and splendor. At the top of the Pass the air seems to glitter against the snow as you look down over herringboned ridges into the Lahaul Valley), visit Solang Valley and , Enjoy skiing, paragliding and other adventurous activities (Cost not included), Return to hotel by evening, Dinner and Overnight stay at Hotel\";i:4;s:238:\"MEALS: Breakfast and dinner only \r\nAfter breakfast, prepare for whole day sightseeing tour to Kullu Valley, which includes - Vaishno Devi Temple, Kullu Shawl industry, Kasol Valley, Manikaran Shiv Temple and Gurudwara. Overnight at hotel.\";i:5;s:196:\"MEALS: Breakfast Only \r\nAfter breakfast day is free for shopping on The Mall, Bid adieu to Manali with lifetime memories and take evening Volvo coach at 16:30 Hrs to Delhi, Overnight on the board.\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:5:{i:1;s:322:\"&lt;p&gt;MEALS: No Meal &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Evening take the Volvo bus at 05:00 PM from Majnu ka tilla metro station or as directed by us and board to Manali. Overnight journey by Volvo. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REPORTING TIME: 05:00 PM &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;DEPARTURE TIME: 05:30 PM (There might be delay of 30-45 mints) &lt;/p&gt;\";i:2;s:798:\"&lt;p&gt;MEALS: DINNER ONLY. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Arrive Manali in the morning, on arrival pick up by company vehicle and transfer to your respected hotel, check in hotel. After fresh up and breakfast, proceed for Manali Sightseeing which includes Hadimba Devi temple is a four-tiered pagoda-like wooden temple standing in deodar trees and has beautiful carvings on its ornamental door. Dedicated to Hadimba, the wife of Bhim, this temple is the venue for an annual fair held during May. Natural Vashisth [known for medicinal use] is located across the Beas River, about 3 km away from Manali, at an altitude of 1,982 meters (6,200 feet) and is the natural sulphur hot springs. Club House, Tibetan Monastery, Van Vihar and The Mall Road back to hotel, dinner and rest overnight in leisure. &lt;/p&gt;\";i:3;s:619:\"&lt;p&gt;MEALS: Breakfast and dinner only &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;After breakfast visit to Rohtang Pass/ Snow Point (Situated about 51 km from Manali town at an altitude of 4,111 meters (13,400 ft.) on the highway to Keylong, is Rohtang Pass. Here one sees the majesty of the mountains at its height and splendor. At the top of the Pass the air seems to glitter against the snow as you look down over herringboned ridges into the Lahaul Valley), visit Solang Valley and , Enjoy skiing, paragliding and other adventurous activities (Cost not included), Return to hotel by evening, Dinner and Overnight stay at Hotel&lt;/p&gt;\";i:4;s:274:\"&lt;p&gt;MEALS: Breakfast and dinner only &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, prepare for whole day sightseeing tour to Kullu Valley, which includes - Vaishno Devi Temple, Kullu Shawl industry, Kasol Valley, Manikaran Shiv Temple and Gurudwara. Overnight at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:5;s:232:\"&lt;p&gt;MEALS: Breakfast Only &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;After breakfast day is free for shopping on The Mall, Bid adieu to Manali with lifetime memories and take evening Volvo coach at 16:30 Hrs to Delhi, Overnight on the board.&lt;/p&gt;\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Includes\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:324:\"Welcome drinks on arrival in hotels. (Non alcoholic)\r\n03 Nights accommodation on twin sharing basis.\r\n03 breakfasts and 03 Dinner in Hotel. (Vegetarian)\r\nVolvo Bus tickets from Delhi to Manali and Manali to Delhi.\r\nAll Local Sight Seeing By Individual Taxi.\r\nAssistance on arrival.\r\nCheck in &amp; Check out time at 12 noon.\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:459:\"&lt;li&gt;Welcome drinks on arrival in hotels. (Non alcoholic)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;03 Nights accommodation on twin sharing basis.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;03 breakfasts and 03 Dinner in Hotel. (Vegetarian)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Volvo Bus tickets from Delhi to Manali and Manali to Delhi.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All Local Sight Seeing By Individual Taxi.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Assistance on arrival.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Check in &amp; Check out time at 12 noon.&lt;/li&gt;\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Excludes\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:161:\"4.5% service tax extra on total bill.\r\nAny monument entry fees / camera fees.\r\nAny meal, which is not mentioned above.\r\nAny guide charges.\r\nAny air / train fare.\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:258:\"&lt;li&gt;4.5% service tax extra on total bill.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any monument entry fees / camera fees.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any meal, which is not mentioned above.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any guide charges.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any air / train fare.&lt;/li&gt;\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Frequently asked Questions\";s:9:\"faq_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:40:\"How fit do I need to be to do this trek?\";i:2;s:70:\"How long do we walk every day when doing Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:3;s:50:\"What is the highest altitude reached in this trek?\";i:4;s:54:\"What about battery charging and hot shower facilities?\";i:5;s:49:\"Are there ATMs on the way to Annapurna Base Camp?\";i:6;s:27:\"What about internet access?\";i:7;s:80:\"Is it necessary to hire Guides/trekking agency for Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:8;s:36:\"How much do guides and porters cost?\";}s:11:\"faq_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:265:\"Annapurna Base Camp is a Grade B or a moderately difficult trekking route. So any fit person can do this trek, even if you do not have any previous experience. You should be aware of what to expect and mentally prepare for it. Then, as long as you will to, you can.\";i:2;s:131:\"On average, you walk about 4 to 6 hours per day. One or two days can be as less as 3hrs and one or two days can be as long as 7hrs.\";i:3;s:131:\"The highest altitude reached is 4190m. This is the elevation of Annapurna Base Camp. ABC is the highest we will climb in this trek.\";i:4;s:230:\"Yes, you can charge batteries en route. Charger should be brought. There are hot shower facilities as well. You may have to pay certain amount for both ($1-$2). Negotiate. Also, hot water facility could be free at lower elevation.\";i:5;s:240:\"No. There are no ATMs on this trek route. You will have to draw enough cash in Pokhara or Kathmandu. There are a number of ATMs in these cities. Everything is paid in Nepali rupees. So money should be exchanged before the start of the trek.\";i:6;s:191:\"Yes. Internet can be accessed in most places. Sometimes, there might be some technical problems. Internet in Nepal is not as fast as you are used to and at times you can just lose connection.\";i:7;s:547:\"Not really. It depends on you. If you want, ABC trekking can be done independently. You could hire a guide and a porter by yourself instead of going through an agency or not hire a guide at all. Although, not having a guide can be a little problematic during off season.\r\n\r\nIt really depends on you. Is it your first time in Nepal? How confident are you of being able to find your way around? How pressed on time are you? If you go through an agency, it will be costlier but everything will be planned. You will only have to come, trek and return.\";i:8;s:103:\"For Annapurna region, pay for guides range from $20 to $30 per day and porters take $15 to $25 per day.\";}}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
