(671, 267, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:10:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:5:\"14999\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:5:\"11157\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"9\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"8\";s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:128:\"&lt;strong&gt;DESTINATIONS COVERED :&lt;/strong&gt; (Delhi 02 Nights)(Shimla 02 Nights )(Manali 03 Nights)(Chandigarh 01 Night)\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:47:\"Delhi Arrival-Local (Delhi is closed On Monday)\";i:2;s:17:\"Delhi- Agra-Delhi\";i:3;s:29:\"Delhi-Shimla (370 Kms- 9 Hrs)\";i:4;s:50:\"Shimla-Kufri-Shimlav Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner\";i:5;s:44:\"Shimla-Manali-Via Manikaran and Kullu Valley\";i:6;s:0:\"\";i:7;s:12:\"Manali Local\";i:8;s:26:\"Manali-Chandigarh (350 km)\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:532:\"Meals: Dinner On arrival at Airport/Railway Station by Morning you will be met, assisted and drive towards hotel .Check-In to the hotel. After taking some rest in the hotel, proceed to panoramic city tour of Delhi. See the Red Fort, a symbol of Mughal power. Also Visit Chandni Chowk (old shopping street) .On return, visit Raj Ghat, a memorial of the great Mahatma Gandhi. Afternoon proceed for a city tour of New Delhi - Sightseeing tour of New Delhi. Visit Lotus Temple, Iskon Temple, Akshar Dham Temple. Overnight stay at hotel.\";i:2;s:237:\"Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After breakfast Early Morning proceeds towards Agra. Distance between Delhi and Agra is 193 Km. Visit the Famous Taj Mahal &amp; Agra Fort via Mathura Vrindavan. Drive Back to Delhi. Overnight stay at Delhi.\";i:3;s:114:\"Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After Breakfast Check Out From the Hotel .Drive to Shimla. Overnight stay in Shimla.\";i:4;s:256:\"After breakfast explore Shimla City .Visit Jakhu temple and Kufri. Kufri situated at an altitude of 2500 meters just an hour\'s drive from Shimla. In the evening Visit Ridge &amp; Mall Road, Scandal Point, Kali Bari, Gaiety Theater. Overnight stay at Hotel.\";i:5;s:234:\"Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After breakfast you will proceed by road to Manali (274 kms / 7hrs). On the way sight-seeing like Sundernagar Lake, Pandoh dam, Vaishno Devi Temple, Kullu, Manikaran and overnight stay at hotel in Manali.\";i:6;s:0:\"\";i:7;s:595:\"Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After breakfast visit &quot;Hadimba temple&quot;. It was built in 1553 with a superbly crafted four tiered pagoda roof; it is famous for its exquisitely carved doorway. &quot;club house&quot; The Club House with its comprehensive facilities that include a roller skating rink, an auditorium, billiards rooms, a library, a bar and restaurant makes wonderful outing for the day.&quot; Tibetan Monastery, Van Vihar, and &quot;Vashisth&quot; Well known for its hot springs. There are old temples dedicated to the sage Vashisth and to Lord Rama. Overnight stay in Hotel.\";i:8;s:230:\"Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After breakfast, check out of the hotel and drive to Chandigarh. Arrive Chandigarh in the evening and check into the hotel. Later in the evening visit Sukhna Lake in Chandigarh Overnight in the hotel.\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:8:{i:1;s:551:\"&lt;p&gt;Meals: Dinner On arrival at Airport/Railway Station by Morning you will be met, assisted and drive towards hotel .Check-In to the hotel. After taking some rest in the hotel, proceed to panoramic city tour of Delhi. See the Red Fort, a symbol of Mughal power. Also Visit Chandni Chowk (old shopping street) .On return, visit Raj Ghat, a memorial of the great Mahatma Gandhi. Afternoon proceed for a city tour of New Delhi - Sightseeing tour of New Delhi. Visit Lotus Temple, Iskon Temple, Akshar Dham Temple. Overnight stay at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:2;s:256:\"&lt;p&gt;Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After breakfast Early Morning proceeds towards Agra. Distance between Delhi and Agra is 193 Km. Visit the Famous Taj Mahal &amp; Agra Fort via Mathura Vrindavan. Drive Back to Delhi. Overnight stay at Delhi.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:3;s:133:\"&lt;p&gt;Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After Breakfast Check Out From the Hotel .Drive to Shimla. Overnight stay in Shimla.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:4;s:275:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast explore Shimla City .Visit Jakhu temple and Kufri. Kufri situated at an altitude of 2500 meters just an hour\'s drive from Shimla. In the evening Visit Ridge &amp; Mall Road, Scandal Point, Kali Bari, Gaiety Theater. Overnight stay at Hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:5;s:253:\"&lt;p&gt;Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After breakfast you will proceed by road to Manali (274 kms / 7hrs). On the way sight-seeing like Sundernagar Lake, Pandoh dam, Vaishno Devi Temple, Kullu, Manikaran and overnight stay at hotel in Manali.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:6;s:19:\"&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";i:7;s:614:\"&lt;p&gt;Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After breakfast visit &quot;Hadimba temple&quot;. It was built in 1553 with a superbly crafted four tiered pagoda roof; it is famous for its exquisitely carved doorway. &quot;club house&quot; The Club House with its comprehensive facilities that include a roller skating rink, an auditorium, billiards rooms, a library, a bar and restaurant makes wonderful outing for the day.&quot; Tibetan Monastery, Van Vihar, and &quot;Vashisth&quot; Well known for its hot springs. There are old temples dedicated to the sage Vashisth and to Lord Rama. Overnight stay in Hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:8;s:249:\"&lt;p&gt;Meals: Breakfast &amp; dinner After breakfast, check out of the hotel and drive to Chandigarh. Arrive Chandigarh in the evening and check into the hotel. Later in the evening visit Sukhna Lake in Chandigarh Overnight in the hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Includes\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:262:\"Welcome drinks on arrival in hotels. (Non alcoholic)\r\n8 Nights accommodation on twin sharing basis.\r\n8 bed tea 8 breakfasts and 8 Dinner in Hotel.\r\nTransport services by an exclusive vehicle as per itinerary.\r\nBus Station and Hotel Pickup\r\nAssistance on arrival.\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:378:\"&lt;li&gt;Welcome drinks on arrival in hotels. (Non alcoholic)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;8 Nights accommodation on twin sharing basis.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;8 bed tea 8 breakfasts and 8 Dinner in Hotel.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Transport services by an exclusive vehicle as per itinerary.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bus Station and Hotel Pickup&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Assistance on arrival.&lt;/li&gt;\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Excludes\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:158:\"Any monument entry fees / camera fees.\r\nAny meal, which is not mentioned above.\r\nAny guide charges.\r\nAny air / train fare.\r\n4.5% Government service tax extra.\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:255:\"&lt;li&gt;Any monument entry fees / camera fees.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any meal, which is not mentioned above.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any guide charges.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any air / train fare.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;4.5% Government service tax extra.&lt;/li&gt;\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Frequently asked Questions\";s:9:\"faq_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:40:\"How fit do I need to be to do this trek?\";i:2;s:70:\"How long do we walk every day when doing Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:3;s:50:\"What is the highest altitude reached in this trek?\";i:4;s:54:\"What about battery charging and hot shower facilities?\";i:5;s:49:\"Are there ATMs on the way to Annapurna Base Camp?\";i:6;s:27:\"What about internet access?\";i:7;s:80:\"Is it necessary to hire Guides/trekking agency for Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:8;s:36:\"How much do guides and porters cost?\";}s:11:\"faq_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:265:\"Annapurna Base Camp is a Grade B or a moderately difficult trekking route. So any fit person can do this trek, even if you do not have any previous experience. You should be aware of what to expect and mentally prepare for it. Then, as long as you will to, you can.\";i:2;s:131:\"On average, you walk about 4 to 6 hours per day. One or two days can be as less as 3hrs and one or two days can be as long as 7hrs.\";i:3;s:131:\"The highest altitude reached is 4190m. This is the elevation of Annapurna Base Camp. ABC is the highest we will climb in this trek.\";i:4;s:230:\"Yes, you can charge batteries en route. Charger should be brought. There are hot shower facilities as well. You may have to pay certain amount for both ($1-$2). Negotiate. Also, hot water facility could be free at lower elevation.\";i:5;s:240:\"No. There are no ATMs on this trek route. You will have to draw enough cash in Pokhara or Kathmandu. There are a number of ATMs in these cities. Everything is paid in Nepali rupees. So money should be exchanged before the start of the trek.\";i:6;s:191:\"Yes. Internet can be accessed in most places. Sometimes, there might be some technical problems. Internet in Nepal is not as fast as you are used to and at times you can just lose connection.\";i:7;s:547:\"Not really. It depends on you. If you want, ABC trekking can be done independently. You could hire a guide and a porter by yourself instead of going through an agency or not hire a guide at all. Although, not having a guide can be a little problematic during off season.\r\n\r\nIt really depends on you. Is it your first time in Nepal? How confident are you of being able to find your way around? How pressed on time are you? If you go through an agency, it will be costlier but everything will be planned. You will only have to come, trek and return.\";i:8;s:103:\"For Annapurna region, pay for guides range from $20 to $30 per day and porters take $15 to $25 per day.\";}}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
