(778, 534, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:10:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:5:\"35999\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:5:\"22999\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:2:\"10\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"9\";s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:10:{i:1;s:36:\"Delhi - Kasauli (304 kms 6 to 7 hrs)\";i:2;s:49:\"Kasauli – Chail-Kufri-Shimla (62 kms 2 to3 hrs)\";i:3;s:24:\"Shimla local sightseeing\";i:4;s:54:\"Shimla- Rewalsar Lake–Prashar Lake (239 kms 7-8 hrs)\";i:5;s:48:\"Prashar Lake-Manikaran-Kasol (106 kms 3to 4 hrs)\";i:6;s:14:\"Arrival Manali\";i:7;s:16:\"Manali city tour\";i:8;s:56:\"Manali- Rohtang pass – Solang valley (80 km 2 to3 hrs)\";i:9;s:36:\"Manali- Chandigarh (320 kms 8-9 hrs)\";i:10;s:61:\"Chandigarh-Local sightseeing- Delhi Drop (260 Kms 4 to 5 hrs)\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:10:{i:1;s:891:\"On arrival at Delhi railway station\\ airport you will met assisted driver and drive for Kasauli .One of the small towns developed by the British during the \'hey day\' of the empire, and reached by a branch road from the Kalka-Shimla road is the quite beautiful hill-station of Kasauli. Kasauli 77 kms from Shimla at 1927 mts is this quaint little town that seems to live in a time warp that belongs to the last century. Its colonial ambience is reinforced by cobbled paths, tiny shops, gabled houses with magnificent facades and scores of neat little gardens and orchards. Kasauli is encircled by a mixed forest of Chir pine, Himalayan oak and huge horse chestnut. Its narrow roads slither up and down the hillsides and offer some interesting vistas. A vantage position for the views is Monkey point, 4 kms from the bus stand. On arrival at Kasauli check in hotel and overnight stay at hotel.\";i:2;s:505:\"This day after breakfast proceed for in and around sightseeing of Kasauli visit Chail and also visit Kufri hail built over three hills, once the proud seat of Maharajah of Patiala, and site of the highest cricket ground in the world. In Chail visit Sidh Baba Ka Mandir, cricket Ground, Wildlife Sanctuary. Visit Kufri India\'s one of the best holidays paradise Kufri in Shimla is beautifully tucked on an altitude of 2,622 meter. The place is a tourist hotspot for its awesome scenic and sports activities.\";i:3;s:385:\"This day after breakfast proceed for local sightseeing stroll in the famous shopping place of Shimla town – &quot;THE MALL &amp; THE RIDGE&quot; This large open space in the heart of town presents excellent views of the mountain ranges. Shimla\'s landmarks – the neo- gothic structure of Christ Church and the neo – Tudor library building – are worth seeing. Overnight at hotel.\";i:4;s:685:\"After breakfast proceed for Prashar Lake. On the way visit Rewalsar Lake, or Tso Pema Lotus Lake, is a mid-altitude lake located on a mountain spur in Mandi district, 22.5 km south-west from Mandi. Its elevation is about 1,360 m above sea level. The sacred lake of Rewalsar is revered by Buddhists, Hindus and Sikhs. Tibetan Buddhists know it as Tso-Pema Lake. On the way see Pandoh lake Prashar Lake is situated at an average height of 2700 meters and lies 45 kms north of Mandi, Himachal Pradesh. It can be reached through two ways one is from Mandi and another one from Bajuara. As soon as the journey in treacherous mountain road ended you saw a beautiful valley and a huge ground.\";i:5;s:260:\"After breakfast check out hotel and proceed to visit unexplored Prashar Lake (subjects to the weather conditions). After that drive for Manikaran. In Manikaran visit Hot Water spring, Shiv Temple and Gurudwara. Back to Kasol dinner and overnight stay at hotel.\";i:6;s:287:\"Early morning after breakfast check out Hotel and drive for Manali Enroot visit Kullu Valley, Vaishno Devi Temple, Kullu Shawl Industries and can do River rafting (subjects to Administration or weather condition). On arrival check in check in to hotel dinner and overnight stay at hotel.\";i:7;s:861:\"Manali, according to legend, was born when the waters of The Great Deluge receded and the seventh Manu\'s ark came to rest on a hillside in this valley. As the earth dried up there came up a place of breathtaking beauty which was named after the great sage. After breakfast, proceed for Manali Sightseeing which includes Hadimba Devi temple is a four-tiered pagoda-like wooden temple standing in deodar trees and has beautiful carvings on its ornamental door. Dedicated to Hadimba, the wife of Bhim, this temple is the venue for an annual fair held during May. Natural Vashisth [known for medicinal use] is located across the Beas River, about 3 km away from Manali, at an altitude of 1,982 meters (6,200 feet) and is the natural sulphur hot springs. Club House, Tibetan Monastery, Van Vihar and The Mall Road back to hotel, dinner and rest overnight in leisure.\";i:8;s:597:\"After breakfast visit to Rohtang Pass/ Snow Point (Situated about 51 km from Manali town at an altitude of 4,111 meters (13,400 ft.) on the highway to Keylong, is Rohtang Pass. Here one sees the majesty of the mountains at its height and splendor. At the top of the Pass the air seems to glitter against the snow as you look down over herringboned ridges into the Lahaul Valley. Enroute visit Kothi, Gulaba, Rahala Falls, Marhi and Solang Valley and Enjoy skiing, paragliding and other adventurous activities (on own cost), later return to the hotel by evening, Dinner and overnight stay at Hotel.\";i:9;s:106:\"After breakfast check out hotel and transfer to Chandigarh. On arrival check in hotel. Overnight at hotel.\";i:10;s:169:\"After breakfast check out hotel visit Rock Garden, Rose Garden, and Sukhna Lake and Sector 17 shopping plaza and transfer to Delhi Railway Station to catch onward Train.\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:10:{i:1;s:0:\"\";i:2;s:0:\"\";i:3;s:0:\"\";i:4;s:0:\"\";i:5;s:0:\"\";i:6;s:0:\"\";i:7;s:0:\"\";i:8;s:0:\"\";i:9;s:0:\"\";i:10;s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:23:\"Package Tour Inclusions\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:200:\"Individual Cab for Entire tour package as per tour plan/itinerary\r\n9 night accommodation for 02 pax on double sharing basis\r\nHotel accommodation on MAP basis (Breakfast + dinner)\r\nAll applicable taxes\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:23:\"Package Tour Exclusions\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:141:\"Monuments entry fees and camera fees\r\nAny which is not mention in above package cost\r\nAny Guide fees/entrainment fees\r\nAny Air and Train fare\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:0:\"\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:1:{s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
